[SN]TITLE[SN]
North Belfast attack: Shots fired through window of house

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A number of shots have been fired at a house in north Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said a bedroom window at a house in Ludlow Square was smashed in the incident which was reported to police at about 22:20 GMT on Thursday.
Two men, aged 21 and 33, were in the house at the time.
One of the men sustained minor cuts to his hand from broken glass. Police believe at least two shots were fired through the window and have appealed for information.
